Contributing to DreamOS

First, thank you for your interest in contributing to DreamOS! 🎉

DreamOS is an ambitious project with the goal of building a lightweight, secure, AI-powered operating system for both PC and mobile devices. Every contribution—whether it's code, documentation, design, testing, or ideas—is appreciated.

---

Before You Start

Please:

- Read the "README.md".
- Read the "CODE_OF_CONDUCT.md".
- Check existing Issues before creating a new one.
- Discuss major features before implementing them.

---

Ways to Contribute

You can help by:

💻 Development

- Fix bugs
- Improve performance
- Develop new features
- Refactor code
- Write tests

📖 Documentation

- Improve documentation
- Fix spelling and grammar
- Write tutorials
- Improve examples

🎨 Design

- UI/UX improvements
- Icons
- Wallpapers
- Animations
- Branding

🧪 Testing

- Report bugs
- Test new features
- Verify fixes
- Performance testing

---

Development Guidelines

Please:

- Write clean, readable code.
- Follow the project's coding standards.
- Keep functions small and maintainable.
- Add comments where necessary.
- Write meaningful commit messages.
- Test your changes before submitting.

---

Commit Message Examples

Good examples:

Add file system caching

Fix memory leak in scheduler

Improve DreamShield performance

Update documentation

Fix UI animation bug

Avoid messages like:

Update

Fix

Changes

Stuff

---

Pull Requests

Before opening a Pull Request:

- Ensure your code builds successfully.
- Test your changes.
- Update documentation if necessary.
- Keep your Pull Request focused on one feature or fix.

---

Reporting Bugs

When reporting a bug, include:

- Operating system
- Version
- Steps to reproduce
- Expected behavior
- Actual behavior
- Screenshots (if applicable)

---

Suggesting Features

Feature requests should include:

- Problem being solved
- Proposed solution
- Possible alternatives
- Additional information

---

Coding Languages

DreamOS may include components written in:

- Rust
- C
- C++
- C#
- Python
- Kotlin
- JavaScript
- HTML
- CSS

Use the language appropriate for the component you're working on.

---

Collaboration

We encourage respectful discussions and teamwork.

Every contribution should help make DreamOS:

- Faster
- More secure
- More reliable
- Easier to use
- Easier to maintain

---

Thank You

Every contribution helps move DreamOS forward.

Thank you for helping build DreamOS.

Dream. Build. Achieve.
